pr_body:
[Evolution Proposal](https://github.com/opencv/opencv/wiki/OE-31.-Julia-Bindings)
Issue: (https://github.com/opencv/opencv/issues/16339) and (https://github.com/opencv/opencv/issues/16233)
[Proposal Abstract](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/projects/#5306473988489216)

Mentors: @vpisarev @americast


This along with #2631 are the final PR for Julia Bindings GSoC project. This PR replaces almost all the code from the previous two phases. This PR link also serves as the final work product link for GSoC 2020 evaluation. 

With this PR merged, opencv's julia module now supports automated generation of bindings that cover most of the functionality present in core,imgproc,imgcodecs,highgui,videoio and dnn module along with some manual binding samples. More details about how to use this module are available at https://github.com/opencv/opencv_contrib/tree/master/modules/julia and https://github.com/opencv/opencv_contrib/blob/master/modules/julia/tutorials/julia.markdown More details about how the bindings work from a technical POV are available at https://archit.me/blog/gsocfinal

### Pull Request Readiness Checklist

See details at https://github.com/opencv/opencv/wiki/How_to_contribute#making-a-good-pull-request

- [x] I agree to contribute to the project under OpenCV (BSD) License.
- [x] To the best of my knowledge, the proposed patch is not based on a code under GPL or other license that is incompatible with OpenCV
- [x] The PR is proposed to proper branch
- [x] There is reference to original bug report and related work
- [x] There is accuracy test, performance test and test data in opencv_extra repository, if applicable
      Patch to opencv_extra has the same branch name.
- [x] The feature is well documented and sample code can be built with the project CMake
